metadata.title: RESEARCH: DNS Query for Zip or Mov Top Level Domain
metadata.description:
A dnsquery event associated with a query for a domain with a top-level-domain of '.zip' or '.mov' was identified. This activity may indicate that a threat actor has crafted a URL that uses a legitimate domain and path as a username to a domain in the '.zip' or '.mov' top level domains. These top level domains therefore masquerade as the file type for URL's target.

Example:
hxxps://github.com∕kubernetes∕kubernetes∕archive∕refs∕tags∕@v1271.zip

In the above example, the username that masquerades as the legitimate domain 'github.com' followed by a path, uses Unicode homoglyphs for forward slash. All of the URL between 'https://' and the '@' symbol is therefore interpreted as a username for the domain 'v1271 dot zip'.
